{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"b462f083"},"source":["# LN Model of Retinal Ganglion Cells\n","\n","**Author**: laquitainesteeve@gmail.com\n","\n","**Students**: ENSTA Paris — Minor in AI\n","\n","**Description**: This notebook models the spiking response of retinal ganglion cells (ON and OFF) to a visual stimulus, using a hierarchy of Linear-Nonlinear (LN) models estimated by maximum likelihood under a Poisson assumption.\n","\n","---\n","## Table of contents\n","1. Imports and Setup  \n","2. Mount Google Drive  \n","3. Load Data  \n","4. PSTH and Stimulus Visualisation  \n","5. Stimulus Pre-processing  \n","6. Stimulus Autocorrelation  \n","7. Spike-Triggered Average (STA) and Linear Filter  \n","8. Linear Prediction  \n","9. ReLU Nonlinearity  \n","10. Full Autocorrelation Correction  \n","11. LN Model — Exponential Nonlinearity (Gradient Descent)  \n","12. Smoothness Regularisation (Laplacian)  \n","13. LN Model — Softplus Nonlinearity  \n","14. Performance Summary  \n","15. Exercises  \n"],"id":"b462f083"},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"dca9d8c5"},"source":["## 1. Imports and Setup"],"id":"dca9d8c5"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"744a40b1","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890589317,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":437,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}}},"source":["import numpy as np                    # numerical computing\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt       # plotting\n","from scipy.io import loadmat          # loading MATLAB .mat files\n","from numpy.linalg import inv          # matrix inversion\n","\n","# Remove top and right spines from all figures for a cleaner look\n","plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 14, 'axes.spines.top': False, 'axes.spines.right': False})\n","\n","# Reproduce MATLAB's default 7-color palette so figures match the reference code\n","MAT_COL = [\n","    '#1f77b4',  # color 1 — blue       (training data)\n","    '#d62728',  # color 2 — red/orange (testing data)\n","    '#e6ac1f',  # color 3 — yellow     (linear filter / linear model)\n","    '#7d3c98',  # color 4 — purple     (full autocorr correction)\n","    '#77b51b',  # color 5 — green      (LN exp model)\n","    '#4dbfee',  # color 6 — light blue (LN exp + regularisation)\n","    '#a31232',  # color 7 — dark red   (LN softplus model)\n","]\n"],"id":"744a40b1","outputs":[],"execution_count":1},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"8e044e8c"},"source":["## 2. Mount Google Drive"],"id":"8e044e8c"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"d604470a","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890647505,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":58186,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"38c4a9d2-552d-4e31-de86-943a29314b63"},"source":["# Mount Google Drive so we can access data files stored there\n","from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')"],"id":"d604470a","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Mounted at /content/drive\n"]}],"execution_count":2},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"776397ca"},"source":["Load the dataset (real stimuli and RGC responses)"],"id":"776397ca"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"75c8c6be","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890652607,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":879,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}}},"source":["# Load the MATLAB data file — adapt the path to match your Drive folder structure\n","from scipy.io import loadmat\n","data = loadmat('/content/drive/MyDrive/ENSTA/dataset.mat')"],"id":"75c8c6be","outputs":[],"execution_count":3},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"a77a942a"},"source":["## 3. Load Data\n","\n","**Expected file:** `dataset.mat`  \n","Contains:\n","- `binnedOFF`: spike counts of an OFF retinal ganglion cell — shape `(R, T)` where R = repetitions, T = time bins  \n","- `binnedON` : spike counts of an ON retinal ganglion cell  \n","- `stim`     :\n","  - full-field flickering light — a single luminance value that changes over time, presented uniformly across the entire visual field (no spatial structure).\n","  - visual stimulus (luminance over time) — shape `(T,)`  \n","- `dt`       : bin width in seconds  "],"id":"a77a942a"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"ad53c78d","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890653520,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":18,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"6a8765bc-ed80-4887-cc14-14c57ece3b0f"},"source":["# Extract each variable from the loaded MATLAB struct\n","binnedOFF = data['binnedOFF']       # OFF-cell spike counts,  shape (R, T)\n","binnedON  = data['binnedON']        # ON-cell spike counts,   shape (R, T)\n","stim      = data['stim'].ravel()    # visual stimulus,        shape (T,)\n","dt        = float(data['dt'])       # time-bin width in seconds\n","\n","R, T = binnedOFF.shape              # R = number of repetitions, T = number of time bins\n","\n","# Integration window: how much stimulus history (0.5 s) we use for the filter\n","integration_time = int(0.5 / dt)    # convert 0.5 s to number of bins\n","\n","print(f\"R={R} repetitions, T={T} time bins, dt={dt}s\")\n","print(f\"Integration time: {integration_time} bins = 0.5 s\")\n"],"id":"ad53c78d","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["R=100 repetitions, T=599 time bins, dt=0.025s\n","Integration time: 20 bins = 0.5 s\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["/tmp/ipykernel_2067/2860756820.py:5: DeprecationWarning: Conversion of an array with ndim > 0 to a scalar is deprecated, and will error in future. Ensure you extract a single element from your array before performing this operation. (Deprecated NumPy 1.25.)\n","  dt        = float(data['dt'])       # time-bin width in seconds\n"]}],"execution_count":4},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"6e0d3cd3"},"source":["## 4. PSTH and Stimulus Visualisation\n","\n","We split data into **training** (first 66%) and **testing** (last 34%) sets.  \n","The **PSTH** (Peri-Stimulus Time Histogram) estimates the mean firing rate across repetitions:\n","\n","$$\\text{PSTH}(t) = \\frac{1}{dt} \\cdot \\frac{1}{R} \\sum_r n_r(t)$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $t$ is the discrete time bin index\n","- $dt$ is the duration of one time bin (seconds)\n","- $R$ is the total number of stimulus repetitions\n","- $r$ is the repetition index, $r = 1, \\ldots, R$\n","- $n_r(t)$ is the spike count in bin $t$ during repetition $r$\n","- $\\text{PSTH}(t)$ is the estimated mean firing rate at time $t$, in Hz\n"],"id":"6e0d3cd3"},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"d2918e9e"},"source":["### Compute"],"id":"d2918e9e"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"c67c19fb","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890658257,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":3,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}}},"source":["# Build index arrays for training and testing time bins\n","# Training starts after 'integration_time' bins (we need that much history for the filter)\n","time_tr = np.arange(integration_time, int(0.66 * T))   # training indices\n","time_te = np.arange(int(0.66 * T), T)                  # testing  indices\n","\n","# Toggle between OFF and ON cell by changing this string\n","cell_type = 'OFF'\n","binned = binnedOFF if cell_type == 'OFF' else binnedON  # select the appropriate cell\n","\n","# Average spike counts across repetitions (axis=0) to get mean count per bin\n","r_tr = binned[:, time_tr].mean(axis=0)   # mean spike count — training\n","r_te = binned[:, time_te].mean(axis=0)   # mean spike count — testing\n","\n","# Convert mean spike count to firing rate in Hz by dividing by bin width\n","psth_tr = r_tr / dt   # PSTH in Hz — training\n","psth_te = r_te / dt   # PSTH in Hz — testing\n"],"id":"c67c19fb","outputs":[],"execution_count":5},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"5dc608b2"},"source":["### Plot"],"id":"5dc608b2"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":491},"id":"ca2e2865","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890660533,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":558,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"8c47715a-5cdd-4aae-827e-3f3f6d5b7a23"},"source":["# Figure 1 — stimulus trace (top) and PSTH split by train/test (bottom)\n","fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 6), sharex=False)\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 1 — Stimulus and PSTH', fontsize=15)\n","\n","# Top panel: raw luminance stimulus over the full recording\n","axes[0].plot(np.arange(T) * dt, stim, 'k', linewidth=2)  # time in seconds on x-axis\n","axes[0].set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n","axes[0].set_ylabel('Luminance')\n","axes[0].set_title('Visual Stimulus')\n","\n","# Bottom panel: PSTH for training and testing periods, colour-coded\n","axes[1].plot(time_tr * dt, psth_tr, linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[0], label='Training')\n","axes[1].plot(time_te * dt, psth_te, linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[1], label='Testing')\n","axes[1].set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n","axes[1].set_ylabel('Spiking Rate (Hz)')\n","axes[1].set_title(f'PSTH — {cell_type} cell')\n","axes[1].legend()\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"id":"ca2e2865","outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":6},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"71c41e39"},"source":["## 5. Stimulus Pre-processing\n","\n","We z-score the stimulus so it has zero mean and unit variance:\n","\n","$$\\tilde{x}(t) = \\frac{x(t) - \\mu_x}{\\sigma_x}$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $x(t)$ is the raw luminance stimulus at time bin $t$\n","- $\\mu_x$ is the mean of $x$ over the full recording\n","- $\\sigma_x$ is the standard deviation of $x$ over the full recording\n","- $\\tilde{x}(t)$ is the resulting z-scored stimulus\n","\n","We then build a **Toeplitz-like design matrix** `full_stim` where each row holds the past stimulus history seen by the neuron up to time $t$:\n","\n","$$\\tilde{X}(t, \\tau) = \\tilde{x}(t - \\tau + 1), \\quad \\tau = 1, \\ldots, T_{\\text{int}}$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $\\tilde{X}(t, \\tau)$ is the entry of the design matrix: the z-scored stimulus value $\\tau$ bins before time $t$\n","- $\\tau$ is the lag index ($\\tau=1$ = present, $\\tau=T_{\\text{int}}$ = most distant past)\n","- $T_{\\text{int}}$ is the integration window length in bins (= 0.5 s / $dt$)\n","\n","Each row `full_stim[t, :]` is ordered from **most distant past** (index 0 = lag −0.5 s) to the **present** (index −1 = lag 0), matching the MATLAB convention.\n"],"id":"71c41e39"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"84ae4b62","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890662105,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":9,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"fed47e11-e705-4325-c51d-7f942017a071"},"source":["# Z-score the stimulus: subtract mean and divide by std so it has zero mean and unit variance\n","stim_tilde = (stim - stim.mean()) / stim.std()\n","\n","# Allocate the design matrix: one row per time bin, one column per lag\n","full_stim = np.zeros((T, integration_time))   # shape (T, integration_time)\n","\n","for tt in range(integration_time, T):\n","    # Slice the past 'integration_time' bins ending at time tt (inclusive)\n","    # NO [::-1] flip — index 0 = oldest lag, index -1 = present, matching MATLAB\n","    full_stim[tt, :] = stim_tilde[tt - integration_time + 1 : tt + 1]\n","\n","print(f\"Design matrix shape: {full_stim.shape}\")   # expected: (T, integration_time)\n"],"id":"84ae4b62","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Design matrix shape: (599, 20)\n"]}],"execution_count":7},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"fc7e7699"},"source":["## 6. Stimulus Autocorrelation\n","\n","The stimulus autocorrelation matrix $C$ quantifies how correlated the stimulus is between any two time lags:\n","\n","$$C(\\tau, \\tau') = \\sum_t \\tilde{x}(t-\\tau) \\cdot \\tilde{x}(t-\\tau')$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $C(\\tau, \\tau')$ is the entry of the autocorrelation matrix at row $\\tau$, column $\\tau'$\n","- $\\tau$ and $\\tau'$ are two lag indices being compared\n","- $\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$ is the z-scored stimulus $\\tau$ bins before time $t$\n","- $t$ sums over all training time bins\n","\n","A flat (white noise) stimulus gives a **diagonal** $C$ (lags are uncorrelated).  \n","A temporally correlated stimulus gives **off-diagonal** entries — nearby lags covary, which biases the STA and must be corrected by multiplying by $C^{-1}$.  \n","**Question:** What does the shape of this matrix tell you about the stimulus statistics?\n"],"id":"fc7e7699"},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"fd07db79"},"source":["### Compute"],"id":"fd07db79"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"57110e9d","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890663118,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":4,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}}},"source":["# Compute the stimulus autocorrelation matrix over the training period\n","# Shape: (integration_time, integration_time)\n","# C[i,j] = sum_t full_stim[t,i] * full_stim[t,j]\n","stim_auto_corr = full_stim[time_tr, :].T @ full_stim[time_tr, :]\n","\n","T_tr = len(time_tr)   # number of training time bins (used for normalisation)\n"],"id":"57110e9d","outputs":[],"execution_count":8},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"2c590425"},"source":["### Plot"],"id":"2c590425"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":407},"id":"6fd540b4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890663999,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":187,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"9bf8c3a7-f358-4924-a18a-a5bc76aaab20"},"source":["# Figure 2 — first row of the autocorrelation matrix (normalised by T_tr)\n","# This shows how the stimulus at one lag correlates with itself at other lags\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 2 — Stimulus Autocorrelation', fontsize=15)\n","\n","ax.plot(np.arange(integration_time) * dt,   # lag axis in seconds\n","        stim_auto_corr[0, :] / T_tr,         # normalised first row\n","        linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[0])\n","ax.set_xlabel('Time lag (s)')\n","ax.set_ylabel('Auto-correlation')\n","ax.set_ylim([0, 1])\n","ax.set_title('Autocorrelation — first row')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"id":"6fd540b4","outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 700x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":9},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"acde4c29"},"source":["## 7. Spike-Triggered Average (STA) and Linear Filter\n","\n","The **STA** is the average stimulus snippet that preceded a spike, giving a first estimate of the neuron's preferred stimulus feature:\n","\n","$$\\text{STA}(\\tau) = \\sum_t \\tilde{r}(t) \\cdot \\tilde{x}(t - \\tau)$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $\\text{STA}(\\tau)$ is the spike-triggered average at lag $\\tau$\n","- $\\tilde{r}(t) = r(t) - \\bar{r}$ is the mean-subtracted spike count at time $t$\n","- $r(t)$ is the mean spike count at time $t$, averaged over repetitions\n","- $\\bar{r}$ is the temporal mean of $r(t)$ over training — this also serves as the model bias $b$\n","- $\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$ is the z-scored stimulus $\\tau$ bins before time $t$\n","\n","The optimal linear filter whitens the STA by correcting for stimulus correlations:\n","\n","$$\\mathbf{w} = \\text{STA} \\cdot C^{-1}$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $\\mathbf{w}$ is the linear filter vector of length $T_{\\text{int}}$\n","- $C^{-1}$ is the inverse of the stimulus autocorrelation matrix — it removes the bias introduced by correlated inputs\n","\n","Here we first use only $\\text{diag}(C)^{-1}$, ignoring off-diagonal terms; the full correction is applied in Section 10.\n"],"id":"acde4c29"},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"d70d1886"},"source":["### Compute"],"id":"d70d1886"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"a6bb7743","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890664909,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":10,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}}},"source":["b = r_tr.mean()           # baseline: mean spike count over training (the model's intercept)\n","r_tr_tilde = r_tr - b     # mean-subtract the response so it fluctuates around zero\n","\n","# STA: cross-correlation between mean-subtracted response and stimulus history\n","# Shape: (integration_time,)  —  STA[tau] = sum_t r_tilde(t) * stim(t-tau)\n","STA = r_tr_tilde @ full_stim[time_tr, :]\n","\n","# Linear filter using only the DIAGONAL of the autocorrelation matrix (ignores correlations)\n","# This is equivalent to normalising each lag independently by its variance\n","w_lin = STA @ inv(np.diag(np.diag(stim_auto_corr)))\n"],"id":"a6bb7743","outputs":[],"execution_count":10},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"b1601d19"},"source":["### Plot"],"id":"b1601d19"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":407},"id":"8d5d4dfd","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890665951,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":199,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"749695ad-1b33-401a-ef06-427e998fd526"},"source":["# Figure 3 — linear filter w_lin as a function of past time lag\n","# x-axis goes from -0.5 s (most distant past) to 0 s (present)\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 3 — Linear Filter (STA / diagonal autocorr)', fontsize=15)\n","\n","ax.plot(np.arange(-integration_time + 1, 1) * dt,   # lag values in seconds\n","        w_lin,\n","        linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[2], label='w linear')\n","ax.axhline(0, color='k', linestyle='--')             # zero reference line\n","ax.set_xlabel('Past time (s)')\n","ax.set_ylabel('Filter weight')\n","ax.set_title('Linear Filter (STA / diagonal autocorr)')\n","ax.legend()\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"id":"8d5d4dfd","outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":11},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ac674765"},"source":["## 8. Linear Gaussian model\n","\n","The linear model predicts the firing rate by projecting the stimulus history onto the filter and adding a bias:\n","\n","$$f(t) = \\mathbf{w} \\cdot \\tilde{X}(t) + b$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $f(t)$ is the predicted (unnormalised) firing rate at time $t$\n","- $\\mathbf{w}$ is the learned linear filter, a vector of length $T_{\\text{int}}$\n","- $\\tilde{X}(t)$ is the row of the design matrix at time $t$ — the past $T_{\\text{int}}$ bins of z-scored stimulus\n","- $b = \\bar{r}$ is the bias (intercept), equal to the mean spike count over training\n","\n","The linear model can produce **negative** values of $f(t)$, which is biologically impossible since firing rates must be $\\geq 0$. The scatter plot in Figure 4 makes this visible and motivates the ReLU in Section 9.  \n","Performance is measured as the **Pearson correlation** $r$ between $f(t)/dt$ and $\\text{PSTH}(t)$ on the test set.\n"],"id":"ac674765"},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"6c60ed30"},"source":["### Compute"],"id":"6c60ed30"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"ad14e907","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890676606,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":3,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"39dbacf4-511b-4dfb-ac81-89c5deaf775c"},"source":["# Apply the linear filter to the test stimulus history to get the predicted firing rate\n","# Shape: (T_te,)\n","f_lin = w_lin @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b   # dot product of filter with each test row, plus bias\n","\n","# Pearson correlation between the test PSTH and the linear prediction (converted to Hz)\n","perf_lin = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_lin / dt)[0, 1]\n","\n","print(f\"Performance — Linear model:  r = {perf_lin:.3f}\")\n"],"id":"ad14e907","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Performance — Linear model:  r = 0.533\n"]}],"execution_count":13},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"6ad83e00"},"source":["### Plot"],"id":"6ad83e00"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":286},"id":"607c12f9","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774890721103,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":824,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"f64e5a65-86d0-4130-c7a2-8bd630e3bbe1"},"source":["# Figure 4 — linear model prediction vs data (time series + scatter)\n","fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 4 — Linear Gaussian Model vs Data', fontsize=15)\n","\n","# Left panel: time series comparison over a 5-second window\n","axes[0].plot(time_te * dt, psth_te,    linewidth=2,   color=MAT_COL[1], label='Data')\n","axes[0].plot(time_te * dt, f_lin / dt, linewidth=1.5, color=MAT_COL[2], label='Linear Gaussian model')\n","axes[0].set_xlim([time_te[0] * dt, time_te[0] * dt + 5])   # zoom into first 5 s of test set\n","axes[0].set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n","axes[0].set_ylabel('Spiking Rate (Hz)')\n","axes[0].set_title('Spiking rate: Data vs Linear Gaussian model')\n","axes[0].legend()\n","\n","# Right panel: scatter plot — reveals negative predictions below the x-axis,\n","# motivating the ReLU truncation in the next section\n","axes[1].scatter(psth_te, f_lin / dt, s=8, alpha=0.5)\n","lim = [min(psth_te.min(), (f_lin/dt).min()),\n","       max(psth_te.max(), (f_lin/dt).max())]  # shared axis limits\n","axes[1].plot(lim, lim, '--k')                  # identity line (perfect prediction)\n","axes[1].set_xlabel('PSTH (Hz)')\n","axes[1].set_ylabel('Linear Gaussian prediction (Hz)')\n","axes[1].set_title('Scatter: Data vs Linear Gaussian prediction')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"id":"607c12f9","outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x400 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":18},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"b9a0af46"},"source":["## 9. ReLU Nonlinearity\n","\n","The **ReLU** (Rectified Linear Unit) clips negative predictions to zero, enforcing the biological constraint that firing rates must be non-negative:\n","\n","$$f_{\\text{ReLU}}(t) = \\max\\bigl(f(t),\\; 0\\bigr)$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $f(t)$ is the raw linear prediction at time $t$ (may be negative)\n","- $f_{\\text{ReLU}}(t)$ is the rectified prediction — guaranteed to be $\\geq 0$\n","\n","After applying ReLU, the scatter plot (Figure 5) shows no points below the $x$-axis, and the Pearson correlation with the PSTH improves because the model no longer outputs physically impossible values.\n"],"id":"b9a0af46"},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"175e1f8b"},"source":["### Compute"],"id":"175e1f8b"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"79f36695","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891111270,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":12,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"fdc6ce65-4a8d-4b47-841f-df4a2f290c28"},"source":["# Apply ReLU: clip all negative predicted rates to zero\n","f_relu = np.maximum(f_lin, 0)   # shape (T_te,)\n","\n","# Pearson correlation with the test PSTH\n","perf_relu = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_relu / dt)[0, 1]\n","\n","print(f\"Performance — Linear + ReLU:  r = {perf_relu:.3f}\")\n"],"id":"79f36695","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Performance — Linear + ReLU:  r = 0.611\n"]}],"execution_count":19},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"239029ba"},"source":["### Plot"],"id":"239029ba"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":286},"id":"d99b2a69","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891113216,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":386,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"0e4474b2-5e70-435f-abea-0a28b80bab65"},"source":["# Figure 5 — ReLU model prediction vs data (time series + scatter)\n","fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 5 — ReLU Model vs Data', fontsize=15)\n","\n","# Left panel: time series — compare the ReLU-clipped prediction to the true PSTH\n","axes[0].plot(time_te * dt, psth_te,     linewidth=2,   color=MAT_COL[1], label='Data')\n","axes[0].plot(time_te * dt, f_relu / dt, linewidth=1.5, color=MAT_COL[2], label='ReLU model')\n","axes[0].set_xlim([time_te[0] * dt, time_te[0] * dt + 5])   # zoom into first 5 s\n","axes[0].set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n","axes[0].set_ylabel('Spiking Rate (Hz)')\n","axes[0].set_title('Spiking rate: Data vs ReLU model')\n","axes[0].legend()\n","\n","# Right panel: scatter — all predictions should now be ≥ 0 (no points below x-axis)\n","axes[1].scatter(psth_te, f_relu / dt, s=8, alpha=0.5)\n","lim = [min(psth_te.min(), (f_relu/dt).min()),\n","       max(psth_te.max(), (f_relu/dt).max())]   # shared axis limits\n","axes[1].plot(lim, lim, '--k')                    # identity line\n","axes[1].set_xlabel('PSTH (Hz)')\n","axes[1].set_ylabel('ReLU prediction (Hz)')\n","axes[1].set_title('Scatter: Data vs ReLU prediction')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"id":"d99b2a69","outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x400 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":20},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"a144e4f5"},"source":["## 10. Full Autocorrelation Correction\n","\n","We now use the **full** inverse autocorrelation matrix rather than only its diagonal, which properly whitens the stimulus:\n","\n","$$\\mathbf{w}_{\\text{AC}} = \\text{STA} \\cdot C^{-1}$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $\\mathbf{w}_{\\text{AC}}$ is the linear filter estimated with the full autocorrelation correction\n","- $\\text{STA}$ is the spike-triggered average vector (see Section 7)\n","- $C$ is the full stimulus autocorrelation matrix of shape $(T_{\\text{int}} \\times T_{\\text{int}})$\n","- $C^{-1}$ is the matrix inverse of $C$ — it removes the bias from correlated stimulus lags, whereas $\\text{diag}(C)^{-1}$ only normalised each lag independently\n"],"id":"a144e4f5"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Compute"],"metadata":{"id":"aAyacPlQVaEm"},"id":"aAyacPlQVaEm"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"7091609b","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891176476,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":5,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"420c4619-c5bf-4628-ee8b-0ea96496c36b"},"source":["# Recompute the linear filter using the FULL autocorrelation matrix (off-diagonals included)\n","# This whitens the stimulus and yields a sharper, less biased filter estimate\n","w_lin_ac = STA @ inv(stim_auto_corr)\n","\n","# Apply the corrected filter to the test set and clip negative rates with ReLU\n","f_relu_ac = np.maximum(w_lin_ac @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b, 0)\n","\n","# Pearson correlation on the test set\n","perf_relu_ac = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_relu_ac / dt)[0, 1]\n","print(f\"Performance — Linear + ReLU + full autocorr:  r = {perf_relu_ac:.3f}\")\n"],"id":"7091609b","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Performance — Linear + ReLU + full autocorr:  r = 0.707\n"]}],"execution_count":21},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Plot"],"metadata":{"id":"938w4ir6VYHP"},"id":"938w4ir6VYHP"},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","# Figure 6 — compare diagonal-only filter vs full-autocorrelation filter\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 6 — Filters: Diagonal vs Full Autocorr', fontsize=15)\n","\n","ax.plot(np.arange(-integration_time + 1, 1) * dt, w_lin,\n","        linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[2], label='w linear')           # diagonal-only filter\n","ax.plot(np.arange(-integration_time + 1, 1) * dt, w_lin_ac,\n","        linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[3], label='w linear + autocorr') # full-autocorr filter\n","ax.axhline(0, color='k', linestyle='--')   # zero reference\n","ax.set_xlabel('Past time (s)')\n","ax.set_ylabel('Filter weight')\n","ax.set_title('Filters: diagonal vs full autocorr')\n","ax.legend()\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":407},"id":"5zLkP_b-VXsh","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891201026,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":270,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"b7a3efb3-02a9-4e04-b1ac-da5ba7180fe6"},"id":"5zLkP_b-VXsh","execution_count":22,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"72d3d392"},"source":["## 11. LN Model — Exponential Nonlinearity (Gradient Descent)\n","\n","The **Poisson LN model** replaces the ReLU with a smooth exponential nonlinearity, guaranteeing strictly positive rates and enabling maximum-likelihood estimation:\n","\n","$$f(t) = \\exp\\!\\left(\\sum_\\tau w(\\tau)\\,\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau) + b\\right)$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $f(t)$ is the predicted firing rate (spikes/bin) at time $t$ — always $> 0$\n","- $w(\\tau)$ is the filter weight at lag $\\tau$; $\\mathbf{w}$ collects all weights into a vector\n","- $\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$ is the z-scored stimulus $\\tau$ bins before $t$\n","- $b$ is a scalar bias (interpretable as the log of the baseline firing rate)\n","\n","Under a Poisson spiking assumption, the log-likelihood of observing $r(t)$ spikes is:\n","\n","$$L = \\frac{1}{T}\\sum_t \\Bigl[ r(t)\\ln f(t) - f(t) \\Bigr]$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $L$ is the mean Poisson log-likelihood over training time bins\n","- $r(t)$ is the observed mean spike count at time $t$\n","- $T$ is the number of training time bins\n","\n","We maximise $L$ by gradient ascent with the following gradients:\n","\n","$$\\nabla_w L = \\frac{1}{T}\\sum_t \\bigl(r(t) - f(t)\\bigr)\\,\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$$\n","\n","$$\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial b} = \\frac{1}{T}\\sum_t \\bigl(r(t) - f(t)\\bigr)$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $\\nabla_w L$ is the gradient of $L$ with respect to each filter weight $w(\\tau)$\n","- $r(t) - f(t)$ is the residual between observed and predicted spike counts\n","- $\\eta$ is the learning rate (step size); weights are updated as $\\mathbf{w} \\leftarrow \\mathbf{w} + \\eta\\,\\nabla_wL$\n"],"id":"72d3d392"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Compute"],"metadata":{"id":"sd0gwyXiVUPD"},"id":"sd0gwyXiVUPD"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"358371a2","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891349572,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":74,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}}},"source":["N_iter = 500    # number of gradient-descent iterations\n","eta    = 1e-1   # learning rate (step size)\n","\n","# Initialise weights near zero to break symmetry, bias at zero\n","w_ln = 1e-9 * np.random.randn(integration_time)   # filter weights, shape (integration_time,)\n","b_ln = 0.0                                          # bias scalar\n","\n","T_tr = len(time_tr)   # number of training bins (for gradient normalisation)\n","T_te = len(time_te)   # number of testing  bins\n","\n","L_tr = np.zeros(N_iter)   # store training log-likelihood at each iteration\n","L_te = np.zeros(N_iter)   # store testing  log-likelihood at each iteration\n","\n","for i in range(N_iter):\n","\n","    # Forward pass: predicted firing rate under the exponential nonlinearity\n","    f_tr = np.exp(w_ln @ full_stim[time_tr, :].T + b_ln)   # shape (T_tr,)\n","    f_te = np.exp(w_ln @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln)   # shape (T_te,)\n","\n","    # Poisson log-likelihood: E[r*log(f) - f]  (up to a constant)\n","    L_tr[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_tr) * r_tr - f_tr)   # scalar — training LL\n","    L_te[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_te) * r_te - f_te)   # scalar — test LL (monitoring only)\n","\n","    # Gradients of the log-likelihood w.r.t. weights and bias\n","    dL_w = (r_tr - f_tr) @ full_stim[time_tr, :] / T_tr   # shape (integration_time,)\n","    dL_b = np.sum(r_tr - f_tr) / T_tr                      # scalar\n","\n","    # Gradient ascent update (we maximise, not minimise)\n","    w_ln += eta * dL_w\n","    b_ln += eta * dL_b\n"],"id":"358371a2","outputs":[],"execution_count":23},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Plot"],"metadata":{"id":"IUHJHcOAVTKo"},"id":"IUHJHcOAVTKo"},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","# Figure 7 — training and test log-likelihood curves across iterations\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 7 — LN Model (exp): Training Curve', fontsize=15)\n","\n","ax.plot(L_tr, '--', linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[4], label='Log-L train')   # dashed = train\n","ax.plot(L_te,       linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[4], label='Log-L test')    # solid  = test\n","ax.set_xlabel('Epoch')\n","ax.set_ylabel('Log-Likelihood')\n","ax.set_title('LN model (exp) — Training curve')\n","ax.legend(loc='lower right')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n","\n","# Evaluate final filter on the test set\n","f_ln_te = np.exp(w_ln @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln)   # predicted rates on test set\n","perf_ln = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_ln_te / dt)[0, 1]         # Pearson r\n","print(f\"Performance — LN model (exp):  r = {perf_ln:.3f}\")\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":425},"id":"SzNVIuuvVSqQ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891350977,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":287,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"daba8f40-177e-4487-c08c-8c8cfdca6a06"},"id":"SzNVIuuvVSqQ","execution_count":24,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Performance — LN model (exp):  r = 0.661\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"6f47f85e"},"source":["## 12. Smoothness Regularisation (Laplacian)\n","\n","Without regularisation the gradient-descent filter can be noisy. We add a **Laplacian** penalty that penalises large differences between adjacent filter weights, favouring smooth temporal profiles:\n","\n","$$L_{\\text{reg}} = L - \\frac{\\lambda}{2}\\,\\mathbf{w} L \\mathbf{w}^\\top$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $L_{\\text{reg}}$ is the regularised objective to be maximised\n","- $L$ is the unregularised Poisson log-likelihood (Section 11)\n","- $\\lambda$ is the regularisation strength — larger $\\lambda$ produces a smoother filter; it should be tuned on a held-out validation set\n","- $\\mathbf{w}$ is the filter weight vector of length $T_{\\text{int}}$\n","- $L$ is the Laplacian (second-difference) matrix of shape $(T_{\\text{int}} \\times T_{\\text{int}})$, with $L_{ii}=4$, $L_{i,i\\pm1}=-1$ (boundary entries $= 2$)\n","- $\\mathbf{w} L \\mathbf{w}^\\top$ is a scalar penalty proportional to $\\sum_\\tau (w(\\tau)-w(\\tau+1))^2$, which is large when the filter oscillates rapidly\n","\n","The regularised gradient is:\n","\n","$$\\nabla_w L_{\\text{reg}} = \\nabla_w L - \\lambda\\,\\mathbf{w} L$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $\\nabla_w L$ is the unregularised gradient (Section 11)\n","- $\\lambda\\,\\mathbf{w} L$ is the gradient of the penalty term — it pulls adjacent weights closer together\n"],"id":"6f47f85e"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Compute"],"metadata":{"id":"9S0SjGuJVP2V"},"id":"9S0SjGuJVP2V"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"37df5c28","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891629888,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":66,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"6ef8b990-6bea-47cd-d0d1-c84a2a9ff6e2"},"source":["# Build the Laplacian (second-difference) matrix of size (integration_time x integration_time)\n","# L[i,i] = 4, L[i,i±1] = -1  (interior); boundary entries are 2 instead of 4\n","L_mat = 4 * np.eye(integration_time)                              # main diagonal\n","L_mat -= np.diag(np.ones(integration_time - 1), 1)               # upper off-diagonal\n","L_mat -= np.diag(np.ones(integration_time - 1), -1)              # lower off-diagonal\n","L_mat[0, 0]   = 2   # boundary correction: first element\n","L_mat[-1, -1] = 2   # boundary correction: last element\n","\n","lambda_reg = 0.15   # regularisation strength — controls smoothness vs data fit\n","\n","# Initialise weights and bias for the regularised model\n","w_ln_reg = 1e-9 * np.random.randn(integration_time)   # shape (integration_time,)\n","b_ln_reg = 0.0\n","\n","L_tr_reg = np.zeros(N_iter)   # regularised training LL per iteration\n","L_te_reg = np.zeros(N_iter)   # regularised test     LL per iteration\n","\n","for i in range(N_iter):\n","\n","    # Forward pass with current regularised filter\n","    f_tr_reg = np.exp(w_ln_reg @ full_stim[time_tr, :].T + b_ln_reg)   # shape (T_tr,)\n","    f_te_reg = np.exp(w_ln_reg @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln_reg)   # shape (T_te,)\n","\n","    # Regularised log-likelihood: standard LL minus smoothness penalty\n","    L_tr_reg[i] = (np.mean(np.log(f_tr_reg) * r_tr - f_tr_reg)\n","                   - 0.5 * lambda_reg * w_ln_reg @ L_mat @ w_ln_reg)   # scalar\n","    L_te_reg[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_te_reg) * r_te - f_te_reg)          # no penalty on test\n","\n","    # Gradient of regularised LL: standard gradient minus Laplacian penalty gradient\n","    dL_w = ((r_tr - f_tr_reg) @ full_stim[time_tr, :] / T_tr\n","            - lambda_reg * w_ln_reg @ L_mat)   # shape (integration_time,)\n","    dL_b = np.sum(r_tr - f_tr_reg) / T_tr      # scalar\n","\n","    # Gradient ascent update\n","    w_ln_reg += eta * dL_w\n","    b_ln_reg += eta * dL_b\n","\n","# Evaluate regularised model on the test set\n","f_ln_reg_te = np.exp(w_ln_reg @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln_reg)   # shape (T_te,)\n","perf_ln_reg = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_ln_reg_te / dt)[0, 1]             # Pearson r\n","print(f\"Performance — LN model + regularisation:  r = {perf_ln_reg:.3f}\")\n"],"id":"37df5c28","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Performance — LN model + regularisation:  r = 0.716\n"]}],"execution_count":25},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Plot"],"metadata":{"id":"buiHoJlaVORE"},"id":"buiHoJlaVORE"},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","# Figure 8 — compare all four filters side by side\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 8 — Filter Comparison (all models)', fontsize=15)\n","\n","tau = np.arange(-integration_time + 1, 1) * dt   # lag axis in seconds\n","\n","ax.plot(tau, w_lin,    linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[2], label='w linear')            # STA / diag\n","ax.plot(tau, w_lin_ac, linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[3], label='w linear + autocorr') # full C\n","ax.plot(tau, w_ln,     linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[4], label='w LN (exp)')           # MLE exp\n","ax.plot(tau, w_ln_reg, linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[5], label='w LN (exp) + reg')    # MLE + reg\n","ax.axhline(0, color='k', linestyle='--')   # zero reference\n","ax.set_xlabel('Past time (s)')\n","ax.set_ylabel('Filter weight')\n","ax.set_title('Filter comparison')\n","ax.legend()\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":407},"id":"J3pYc8jzVNcA","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891632594,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":245,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"db345fb1-5b06-490b-e398-f40b64a6c542"},"id":"J3pYc8jzVNcA","execution_count":26,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 900x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"c069f289"},"source":["## 13. LN Model — Softplus Nonlinearity\n","\n","**Softplus** is a smooth approximation of ReLU that is differentiable everywhere, making gradient-based optimisation more stable near zero:\n","\n","$$\\text{softplus}(x) = \\log(1 + e^x)$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $x$ is the scalar pre-activation input to the nonlinearity\n","\n","Its derivative is the **sigmoid** function:\n","\n","$$\\frac{d}{dx}\\text{softplus}(x) = \\sigma(x) = \\frac{1}{1+e^{-x}}$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $\\sigma(x)$ is the sigmoid (logistic) function, valued between 0 and 1\n","\n","The pre-nonlinearity input and predicted rate at each time step are:\n","\n","$$u(t) = \\mathbf{w} \\cdot \\tilde{X}(t) + b, \\qquad f(t) = \\text{softplus}\\bigl(u(t)\\bigr)$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $u(t)$ is the linear pre-activation at time $t$ — the dot product of the filter with the stimulus history plus the bias\n","- $f(t)$ is the predicted firing rate — always $> 0$ since $\\text{softplus}(x) > 0$ for all $x$\n","- $\\mathbf{w}$ is the filter weight vector, $\\tilde{X}(t)$ is the stimulus history row, $b$ is the bias\n","\n","The gradient of the Poisson log-likelihood with respect to the filter weights is:\n","\n","$$\\nabla_w L = \\frac{1}{T}\\sum_t \\left(\\frac{r(t)}{f(t)} - 1\\right) \\sigma(u(t))\\,\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$$\n","\n","where:\n","- $r(t)$ is the observed mean spike count at time $t$\n","- $\\frac{r(t)}{f(t)} - 1$ is the residual term — positive when the model under-predicts, negative when it over-predicts\n","- $\\sigma(u(t))$ is the chain-rule factor from differentiating softplus with respect to $u(t)$\n","- $T$ is the number of training time bins\n"],"id":"c069f289"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":302},"id":"393fa14e","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891736440,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":485,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"f45855af-b59e-4caa-9b00-1ce0cbf8265e"},"source":["# Define softplus and its derivative (sigmoid) as lambda functions\n","softplus  = lambda x: np.log1p(np.exp(x))          # log(1 + e^x)\n","dsoftplus = lambda x: 1.0 / (1.0 + np.exp(-x))     # sigmoid: d/dx softplus = sigma(x)\n","\n","# Initialise softplus model weights and bias near zero\n","w_ln_sp = 1e-9 * np.random.randn(integration_time)   # shape (integration_time,)\n","b_ln_sp = 0.0\n","\n","L_tr_sp = np.zeros(N_iter)   # training LL per iteration\n","L_te_sp = np.zeros(N_iter)   # test     LL per iteration\n","\n","for i in range(N_iter):\n","\n","    # Linear projection of stimulus history onto current filter (pre-nonlinearity)\n","    u_tr = w_ln_sp @ full_stim[time_tr, :].T + b_ln_sp   # shape (T_tr,) — \"input\" to nonlinearity\n","    u_te = w_ln_sp @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln_sp   # shape (T_te,)\n","\n","    # Apply softplus nonlinearity to get predicted firing rates\n","    f_tr_sp = softplus(u_tr)   # shape (T_tr,)\n","    f_te_sp = softplus(u_te)   # shape (T_te,)\n","\n","    # Poisson log-likelihood: E[r*log(f) - f]\n","    L_tr_sp[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_tr_sp) * r_tr - f_tr_sp)   # training scalar\n","    L_te_sp[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_te_sp) * r_te - f_te_sp)   # test scalar\n","\n","    # Gradient via chain rule: dLL/du * du/dw\n","    # dLL/df = r/f - 1 ;  df/du = dsoftplus(u) = sigma(u)\n","    dL_w = ((r_tr / f_tr_sp - 1) * dsoftplus(u_tr)) @ full_stim[time_tr, :] / T_tr\n","    dL_b = np.sum((r_tr / f_tr_sp - 1) * dsoftplus(u_tr)) / T_tr   # scalar\n","\n","    # Gradient ascent update\n","    w_ln_sp += eta * dL_w\n","    b_ln_sp += eta * dL_b\n","\n","# Final test-set prediction with the softplus model\n","f_ln_sp_te = softplus(w_ln_sp @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln_sp)   # shape (T_te,)\n","perf_sp = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_ln_sp_te / dt)[0, 1]                  # Pearson r\n","print(f\"Performance — LN model (softplus):  r = {perf_sp:.3f}\")\n","\n","# Figure 9 — left: exp vs softplus filters; right: predictions vs data\n","fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 9 — Softplus Model: Filter and Prediction', fontsize=15)\n","\n","tau = np.arange(-integration_time + 1, 1) * dt   # lag axis in seconds\n","\n","# Left panel: overlay the exp-nonlinearity filter and the softplus filter\n","axes[0].plot(tau, w_ln,    linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[4], label='w LN exp')       # exp model\n","axes[0].plot(tau, w_ln_sp, linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[5], label='w LN softplus')  # softplus model\n","axes[0].axhline(0, color='k', linestyle='--')   # zero reference\n","axes[0].set_xlabel('Past time (s)')\n","axes[0].set_ylabel('Filter weight')\n","axes[0].set_title('Filter: exp vs softplus')\n","axes[0].legend()\n","\n","# Right panel: compare both model predictions to the measured PSTH\n","axes[1].plot(time_te * dt, psth_te,          linewidth=2,   color=MAT_COL[1], label='Data')\n","axes[1].plot(time_te * dt, f_ln_te   / dt,   linewidth=1.5, color=MAT_COL[4], label='LN exp')\n","axes[1].plot(time_te * dt, f_ln_sp_te / dt,  linewidth=1.5, color=MAT_COL[5], label='LN softplus')\n","axes[1].set_xlim([time_te[0] * dt, time_te[0] * dt + 5])   # zoom into first 5 s of test set\n","axes[1].set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n","axes[1].set_ylabel('Spiking Rate (Hz)')\n","axes[1].set_title('Spiking rate: Data vs LN models')\n","axes[1].legend()\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"id":"393fa14e","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Performance — LN model (softplus):  r = 0.816\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x400 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":27},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"5552c02e"},"source":["## 14. Performance Summary"],"id":"5552c02e"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Compute"],"metadata":{"id":"IKAFdHPvVx82"},"id":"IKAFdHPvVx82"},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"94e01a2b","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891751008,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":6,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"ee21c210-6ae6-4aea-a126-697043cf24ca"},"source":["# Collect Pearson r for every model on the test set\n","models = {\n","    'Linear':              np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_lin      / dt)[0, 1],\n","    'Linear + ReLU':       np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_relu     / dt)[0, 1],\n","    'Linear + ReLU + AC':  np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_relu_ac  / dt)[0, 1],\n","    'LN exp':              np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_ln_te    / dt)[0, 1],\n","    'LN exp + reg':        np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_ln_reg_te/ dt)[0, 1],\n","    'LN softplus':         np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_ln_sp_te / dt)[0, 1],\n","}\n","\n","# Print a formatted table of results\n","print(\"\\nModel Performance (Pearson r on test set)\\n\" + \"-\"*45)\n","for name, r in models.items():\n","    print(f\"  {name:<25} r = {r:.3f}\")"],"id":"94e01a2b","outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Model Performance (Pearson r on test set)\n","---------------------------------------------\n","  Linear                    r = 0.533\n","  Linear + ReLU             r = 0.611\n","  Linear + ReLU + AC        r = 0.707\n","  LN exp                    r = 0.661\n","  LN exp + reg              r = 0.716\n","  LN softplus               r = 0.816\n"]}],"execution_count":28},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Plot"],"metadata":{"id":"pQ7Re-hmVw-q"},"id":"pQ7Re-hmVw-q"},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Figure 10 — horizontal bar chart comparing all models\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 4))\n","fig.suptitle('Figure 10 — Model Comparison', fontsize=15)\n","\n","ax.barh(list(models.keys()),          # model names on y-axis\n","        list(models.values()),         # Pearson r values on x-axis\n","        color=MAT_COL[:len(models)])   # one colour per model\n","ax.set_xlabel('Pearson r (test set)')\n","ax.set_title('Model comparison')\n","ax.set_xlim([0, 1])   # correlation ranges from 0 to 1 for these models\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":407},"id":"PREhIrqYVwan","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774891758217,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":252,"user":{"displayName":"steeve laquitaine","userId":"08351460388525958343"}},"outputId":"f7d2dc3e-e128-460a-8bec-f61fae070cff"},"id":"PREhIrqYVwan","execution_count":29,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 900x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"2a74627b"},"source":["## 15. Exercises\n","\n","**Exercise 1 — Regularisation**\n","- Add **L2 (ridge)** regularisation to the LN model: $L_{\\text{reg}} = L - \\frac{\\lambda}{2} \\|\\mathbf{w}\\|^2$\n","- Compare the resulting filter shape with the Laplacian regularisation\n","- Optimise $\\lambda$ over a validation set (e.g., split training into 80/20)\n","\n","**Exercise 2 — Nonlinearities**\n","- Implement the **ReLU** nonlinearity in the gradient descent framework (hint: the derivative of ReLU is the Heaviside step function)\n","- Compare convergence speed and final performance with exp and softplus\n","\n","**Exercise 3 — ON cell**\n","- Switch `cell_type = 'ON'` in Section 4 and re-run the notebook\n","- How does the shape of the linear filter differ between ON and OFF cells? Why?\n"],"id":"2a74627b"}],"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.10.0"},"colab":{"provenance":[{"file_id":"https://github.com/steevelaquitaine/ensta_teaching/blob/master/2_LN_model_of_RGC.ipynb","timestamp":1774877902717}],"toc_visible":true}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":5}
