        "# LN Model of Retinal Ganglion Cells\n",
        "\n",
        "**Author**: laquitainesteeve@gmail.com\n",
        "\n",
        "**Students**: ENSTA Paris — Minor in AI\n",
        "\n",
        "**Description**: This notebook models the spiking response of retinal ganglion cells (ON and OFF) to a visual stimulus, using a hierarchy of Linear-Nonlinear (LN) models estimated by maximum likelihood under a Poisson assumption.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "## Table of contents\n",
        "1. Imports and Setup  \n",
        "2. Mount Google Drive  \n",
        "3. Load Data  \n",
        "4. PSTH and Stimulus Visualisation  \n",
        "5. Stimulus Pre-processing  \n",
        "6. Stimulus Autocorrelation  \n",
        "7. Spike-Triggered Average (STA) and Linear Filter  \n",
        "8. Linear Prediction  \n",
        "9. ReLU Nonlinearity  \n",
        "10. Full Autocorrelation Correction  \n",
        "11. LN Model — Exponential Nonlinearity (Gradient Descent)  \n",
        "12. Smoothness Regularisation (Laplacian)  \n",
        "13. LN Model — Softplus Nonlinearity  \n",
        "14. Performance Summary  \n",
        "15. Exercises  \n"
      ],
      "id": "b462f083"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dca9d8c5"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 1. Imports and Setup"
      ],
      "id": "dca9d8c5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "744a40b1"
      },
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np                    # numerical computing\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt       # plotting\n",
        "from scipy.io import loadmat          # loading MATLAB .mat files\n",
        "from numpy.linalg import inv          # matrix inversion\n",
        "\n",
        "# Remove top and right spines from all figures for a cleaner look\n",
        "plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 14, 'axes.spines.top': False, 'axes.spines.right': False})\n",
        "\n",
        "# Reproduce MATLAB's default 7-color palette so figures match the reference code\n",
        "MAT_COL = [\n",
        "    '#1f77b4',  # color 1 — blue       (training data)\n",
        "    '#d62728',  # color 2 — red/orange (testing data)\n",
        "    '#e6ac1f',  # color 3 — yellow     (linear filter / linear model)\n",
        "    '#7d3c98',  # color 4 — purple     (full autocorr correction)\n",
        "    '#77b51b',  # color 5 — green      (LN exp model)\n",
        "    '#4dbfee',  # color 6 — light blue (LN exp + regularisation)\n",
        "    '#a31232',  # color 7 — dark red   (LN softplus model)\n",
        "]\n"
      ],
      "id": "744a40b1",
      "outputs": [],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8e044e8c"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 2. Mount Google Drive"
      ],
      "id": "8e044e8c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "d604470a",
        "outputId": "ac5a0c0f-0e5e-4c96-85ab-44b99c586964"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Mount Google Drive so we can access data files stored there\n",
        "from google.colab import drive\n",
        "drive.mount('/content/drive')\n"
      ],
      "id": "d604470a",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Mounted at /content/drive\n"
          ]
        }
