    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "776397ca"
      },
      "source": [
        "Load the dataset (real stimuli and RGC responses)"
      ],
      "id": "776397ca"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "75c8c6be"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Load the MATLAB data file — adapt the path to match your Drive folder structure\n",
        "from scipy.io import loadmat\n",
        "data = loadmat('/content/drive/MyDrive/ENSTA/dataset.mat')\n"
      ],
      "id": "75c8c6be",
      "outputs": [],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a77a942a"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 3. Load Data\n",
        "\n",
        "**Expected file:** `dataset.mat`  \n",
        "Contains:\n",
        "- `binnedOFF`: spike counts of an OFF retinal ganglion cell — shape `(R, T)` where R = repetitions, T = time bins  \n",
        "- `binnedON` : spike counts of an ON retinal ganglion cell  \n",
        "- `stim`     :\n",
        "  - full-field flickering light — a single luminance value that changes over time, presented uniformly across the entire visual field (no spatial structure).\n",
        "  - visual stimulus (luminance over time) — shape `(T,)`  \n",
        "- `dt`       : bin width in seconds  "
      ],
      "id": "a77a942a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "ad53c78d",
        "outputId": "7e084ed9-2941-4612-b7fc-15d926d94e9a"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Extract each variable from the loaded MATLAB struct\n",
        "binnedOFF = data['binnedOFF']       # OFF-cell spike counts,  shape (R, T)\n",
        "binnedON  = data['binnedON']        # ON-cell spike counts,   shape (R, T)\n",
        "stim      = data['stim'].ravel()    # visual stimulus,        shape (T,)\n",
        "dt        = float(data['dt'])       # time-bin width in seconds\n",
        "\n",
        "R, T = binnedOFF.shape              # R = number of repetitions, T = number of time bins\n",
        "\n",
        "# Integration window: how much stimulus history (0.5 s) we use for the filter\n",
        "integration_time = int(0.5 / dt)    # convert 0.5 s to number of bins\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"R={R} repetitions, T={T} time bins, dt={dt}s\")\n",
        "print(f\"Integration time: {integration_time} bins = 0.5 s\")\n"
      ],
      "id": "ad53c78d",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "R=100 repetitions, T=599 time bins, dt=0.025s\n",
            "Integration time: 20 bins = 0.5 s\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stderr",
          "text": [
            "/tmp/ipykernel_355/2860756820.py:5: DeprecationWarning: Conversion of an array with ndim > 0 to a scalar is deprecated, and will error in future. Ensure you extract a single element from your array before performing this operation. (Deprecated NumPy 1.25.)\n",
            "  dt        = float(data['dt'])       # time-bin width in seconds\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6e0d3cd3"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 4. PSTH and Stimulus Visualisation\n",
        "\n",
        "We split data into **training** (first 66%) and **testing** (last 34%) sets.  \n",
        "The **PSTH** (Peri-Stimulus Time Histogram) estimates the mean firing rate across repetitions:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{PSTH}(t) = \\frac{1}{dt} \\cdot \\frac{1}{R} \\sum_r n_r(t)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $t$ is the discrete time bin index\n",
        "- $dt$ is the duration of one time bin (seconds)\n",
        "- $R$ is the total number of stimulus repetitions\n",
        "- $r$ is the repetition index, $r = 1, \\ldots, R$\n",
        "- $n_r(t)$ is the spike count in bin $t$ during repetition $r$\n",
        "- $\\text{PSTH}(t)$ is the estimated mean firing rate at time $t$, in Hz\n"
      ],
      "id": "6e0d3cd3"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d2918e9e"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Compute"
      ],
      "id": "d2918e9e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c67c19fb"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Build index arrays for training and testing time bins\n",
        "# Training starts after 'integration_time' bins (we need that much history for the filter)\n",
        "time_tr = np.arange(integration_time, int(0.66 * T))   # training indices\n",
        "time_te = np.arange(int(0.66 * T), T)                  # testing  indices\n",
        "\n",
        "# Toggle between OFF and ON cell by changing this string\n",
        "cell_type = 'OFF'\n",
        "binned = binnedOFF if cell_type == 'OFF' else binnedON  # select the appropriate cell\n",
        "\n",
        "# Average spike counts across repetitions (axis=0) to get mean count per bin\n",
        "r_tr = binned[:, time_tr].mean(axis=0)   # mean spike count — training\n",
        "r_te = binned[:, time_te].mean(axis=0)   # mean spike count — testing\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert mean spike count to firing rate in Hz by dividing by bin width\n",
        "psth_tr = r_tr / dt   # PSTH in Hz — training\n",
        "psth_te = r_te / dt   # PSTH in Hz — testing\n"
      ],
      "id": "c67c19fb",
      "outputs": [],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5dc608b2"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Plot"
      ],
      "id": "5dc608b2"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 543
        },
        "id": "ca2e2865",
        "outputId": "3e3c4c2b-fa3c-4c18-9704-6025dc00b5d0"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Figure 1 — stimulus trace (top) and PSTH split by train/test (bottom)\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 6), sharex=False)\n",
        "fig.suptitle('Figure 1 — Stimulus and PSTH', fontsize=15)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Top panel: raw luminance stimulus over the full recording\n",
        "axes[0].plot(np.arange(T) * dt, stim, 'k', linewidth=2)  # time in seconds on x-axis\n",
        "axes[0].set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n",
        "axes[0].set_ylabel('Luminance')\n",
        "axes[0].set_title('Visual Stimulus')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Bottom panel: PSTH for training and testing periods, colour-coded\n",
        "axes[1].plot(time_tr * dt, psth_tr, linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[0], label='Training')\n",
        "axes[1].plot(time_te * dt, psth_te, linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[1], label='Testing')\n",
        "axes[1].set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n",
        "axes[1].set_ylabel('Spiking Rate (Hz)')\n",
        "axes[1].set_title(f'PSTH — {cell_type} cell')\n",
        "axes[1].legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "id": "ca2e2865",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "71c41e39"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 5. Stimulus Pre-processing\n",
        "\n",
        "We z-score the stimulus so it has zero mean and unit variance:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\tilde{x}(t) = \\frac{x(t) - \\mu_x}{\\sigma_x}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $x(t)$ is the raw luminance stimulus at time bin $t$\n",
        "- $\\mu_x$ is the mean of $x$ over the full recording\n",
        "- $\\sigma_x$ is the standard deviation of $x$ over the full recording\n",
        "- $\\tilde{x}(t)$ is the resulting z-scored stimulus\n",
        "\n",
        "We then build a **Toeplitz-like design matrix** `full_stim` where each row holds the past stimulus history seen by the neuron up to time $t$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\tilde{X}(t, \\tau) = \\tilde{x}(t - \\tau + 1), \\quad \\tau = 1, \\ldots, T_{\\text{int}}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $\\tilde{X}(t, \\tau)$ is the entry of the design matrix: the z-scored stimulus value $\\tau$ bins before time $t$\n",
        "- $\\tau$ is the lag index ($\\tau=1$ = present, $\\tau=T_{\\text{int}}$ = most distant past)\n",
        "- $T_{\\text{int}}$ is the integration window length in bins (= 0.5 s / $dt$)\n",
        "\n",
        "Each row `full_stim[t, :]` is ordered from **most distant past** (index 0 = lag −0.5 s) to the **present** (index −1 = lag 0), matching the MATLAB convention.\n"
      ],
      "id": "71c41e39"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "84ae4b62",
        "outputId": "0f45cbd7-5fc0-48e7-d980-60044d9d6885"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Z-score the stimulus: subtract mean and divide by std so it has zero mean and unit variance\n",
        "stim_tilde = (stim - stim.mean()) / stim.std()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Allocate the design matrix: one row per time bin, one column per lag\n",
        "full_stim = np.zeros((T, integration_time))   # shape (T, integration_time)\n",
        "\n",
        "for tt in range(integration_time, T):\n",
        "    # Slice the past 'integration_time' bins ending at time tt (inclusive)\n",
        "    # NO [::-1] flip — index 0 = oldest lag, index -1 = present, matching MATLAB\n",
        "    full_stim[tt, :] = stim_tilde[tt - integration_time + 1 : tt + 1]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Design matrix shape: {full_stim.shape}\")   # expected: (T, integration_time)\n"
      ],
      "id": "84ae4b62",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Design matrix shape: (599, 20)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "fc7e7699"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 6. Stimulus Autocorrelation\n",
        "\n",
        "The stimulus autocorrelation matrix $C$ quantifies how correlated the stimulus is between any two time lags:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$C(\\tau, \\tau') = \\sum_t \\tilde{x}(t-\\tau) \\cdot \\tilde{x}(t-\\tau')$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $C(\\tau, \\tau')$ is the entry of the autocorrelation matrix at row $\\tau$, column $\\tau'$\n",
        "- $\\tau$ and $\\tau'$ are two lag indices being compared\n",
        "- $\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$ is the z-scored stimulus $\\tau$ bins before time $t$\n",
        "- $t$ sums over all training time bins\n",
        "\n",
        "A flat (white noise) stimulus gives a **diagonal** $C$ (lags are uncorrelated).  \n",
        "A temporally correlated stimulus gives **off-diagonal** entries — nearby lags covary, which biases the STA and must be corrected by multiplying by $C^{-1}$.  \n",
        "**Question:** What does the shape of this matrix tell you about the stimulus statistics?\n"
      ],
      "id": "fc7e7699"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "fd07db79"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Compute"
      ],
      "id": "fd07db79"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "57110e9d"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Compute the stimulus autocorrelation matrix over the training period\n",
        "# Shape: (integration_time, integration_time)\n",
        "# C[i,j] = sum_t full_stim[t,i] * full_stim[t,j]\n",
        "stim_auto_corr = full_stim[time_tr, :].T @ full_stim[time_tr, :]\n",
        "\n",
        "T_tr = len(time_tr)   # number of training time bins (used for normalisation)\n"
      ],
      "id": "57110e9d",
      "outputs": [],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2c590425"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Plot"
      ],
      "id": "2c590425"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 407
        },
        "id": "6fd540b4",
        "outputId": "52a1cb88-5765-4aaa-afb2-dd7b800aa1d1"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Figure 2 — first row of the autocorrelation matrix (normalised by T_tr)\n",
        "# This shows how the stimulus at one lag correlates with itself at other lags\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 4))\n",
        "fig.suptitle('Figure 2 — Stimulus Autocorrelation', fontsize=15)\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.plot(np.arange(integration_time) * dt,   # lag axis in seconds\n",
        "        stim_auto_corr[0, :] / T_tr,         # normalised first row\n",
        "        linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[0])\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Time lag (s)')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Auto-correlation')\n",
        "ax.set_ylim([0, 1])\n",
        "ax.set_title('Autocorrelation — first row')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "id": "6fd540b4",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 700x400 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "acde4c29"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 7. Spike-Triggered Average (STA) and Linear Filter\n",
        "\n",
        "The **STA** is the average stimulus snippet that preceded a spike, giving a first estimate of the neuron's preferred stimulus feature:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{STA}(\\tau) = \\sum_t \\tilde{r}(t) \\cdot \\tilde{x}(t - \\tau)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $\\text{STA}(\\tau)$ is the spike-triggered average at lag $\\tau$\n",
        "- $\\tilde{r}(t) = r(t) - \\bar{r}$ is the mean-subtracted spike count at time $t$\n",
        "- $r(t)$ is the mean spike count at time $t$, averaged over repetitions\n",
        "- $\\bar{r}$ is the temporal mean of $r(t)$ over training — this also serves as the model bias $b$\n",
        "- $\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$ is the z-scored stimulus $\\tau$ bins before time $t$\n",
        "\n",
        "The optimal linear filter whitens the STA by correcting for stimulus correlations:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\mathbf{w} = \\text{STA} \\cdot C^{-1}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $\\mathbf{w}$ is the linear filter vector of length $T_{\\text{int}}$\n",
        "- $C^{-1}$ is the inverse of the stimulus autocorrelation matrix — it removes the bias introduced by correlated inputs\n",
        "\n",
        "Here we first use only $\\text{diag}(C)^{-1}$, ignoring off-diagonal terms; the full correction is applied in Section 10.\n"
      ],
      "id": "acde4c29"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d70d1886"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Compute"
      ],
      "id": "d70d1886"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a6bb7743"
      },
      "source": [
        "b = r_tr.mean()           # baseline: mean spike count over training (the model's intercept)\n",
        "r_tr_tilde = r_tr - b     # mean-subtract the response so it fluctuates around zero\n",
        "\n",
        "# STA: cross-correlation between mean-subtracted response and stimulus history\n",
        "# Shape: (integration_time,)  —  STA[tau] = sum_t r_tilde(t) * stim(t-tau)\n",
        "STA = r_tr_tilde @ full_stim[time_tr, :]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Linear filter using only the DIAGONAL of the autocorrelation matrix (ignores correlations)\n",
        "# This is equivalent to normalising each lag independently by its variance\n",
        "w_lin = STA @ inv(np.diag(np.diag(stim_auto_corr)))\n"
      ],
      "id": "a6bb7743",
      "outputs": [],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "b1601d19"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Plot"
      ],
      "id": "b1601d19"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 407
        },
        "id": "8d5d4dfd",
        "outputId": "9c41a8ce-06b1-4512-a642-3619141fd650"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Figure 3 — linear filter w_lin as a function of past time lag\n",
        "# x-axis goes from -0.5 s (most distant past) to 0 s (present)\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n",
        "fig.suptitle('Figure 3 — Linear Filter (STA / diagonal autocorr)', fontsize=15)\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.plot(np.arange(-integration_time + 1, 1) * dt,   # lag values in seconds\n",
        "        w_lin,\n",
        "        linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[2], label='w linear')\n",
        "ax.axhline(0, color='k', linestyle='--')             # zero reference line\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Past time (s)')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Filter weight')\n",
        "ax.set_title('Linear Filter (STA / diagonal autocorr)')\n",
        "ax.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "id": "8d5d4dfd",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ac674765"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 8. Linear Prediction\n",
        "\n",
        "The linear model predicts the firing rate by projecting the stimulus history onto the filter and adding a bias:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$f(t) = \\mathbf{w} \\cdot \\tilde{X}(t) + b$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $f(t)$ is the predicted (unnormalised) firing rate at time $t$\n",
        "- $\\mathbf{w}$ is the learned linear filter, a vector of length $T_{\\text{int}}$\n",
        "- $\\tilde{X}(t)$ is the row of the design matrix at time $t$ — the past $T_{\\text{int}}$ bins of z-scored stimulus\n",
        "- $b = \\bar{r}$ is the bias (intercept), equal to the mean spike count over training\n",
        "\n",
        "The linear model can produce **negative** values of $f(t)$, which is biologically impossible since firing rates must be $\\geq 0$. The scatter plot in Figure 4 makes this visible and motivates the ReLU in Section 9.  \n",
        "Performance is measured as the **Pearson correlation** $r$ between $f(t)/dt$ and $\\text{PSTH}(t)$ on the test set.\n"
      ],
      "id": "ac674765"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6c60ed30"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Compute"
      ],
      "id": "6c60ed30"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "ad14e907",
        "outputId": "951f8488-6cf0-4433-f47a-2df0b1298b25"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Apply the linear filter to the test stimulus history to get the predicted firing rate\n",
        "# Shape: (T_te,)\n",
        "f_lin = w_lin @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b   # dot product of filter with each test row, plus bias\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pearson correlation between the test PSTH and the linear prediction (converted to Hz)\n",
        "perf_lin = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_lin / dt)[0, 1]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Performance — Linear model:  r = {perf_lin:.3f}\")\n"
      ],
      "id": "ad14e907",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Performance — Linear model:  r = 0.533\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6ad83e00"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Plot"
      ],
      "id": "6ad83e00"
    },
