    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a144e4f5"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 10. Full Autocorrelation Correction\n",
        "\n",
        "We now use the **full** inverse autocorrelation matrix rather than only its diagonal, which properly whitens the stimulus:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\mathbf{w}_{\\text{AC}} = \\text{STA} \\cdot C^{-1}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $\\mathbf{w}_{\\text{AC}}$ is the linear filter estimated with the full autocorrelation correction\n",
        "- $\\text{STA}$ is the spike-triggered average vector (see Section 7)\n",
        "- $C$ is the full stimulus autocorrelation matrix of shape $(T_{\\text{int}} \\times T_{\\text{int}})$\n",
        "- $C^{-1}$ is the matrix inverse of $C$ — it removes the bias from correlated stimulus lags, whereas $\\text{diag}(C)^{-1}$ only normalised each lag independently\n"
      ],
      "id": "a144e4f5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Compute"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "aAyacPlQVaEm"
      },
      "id": "aAyacPlQVaEm"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "7091609b",
        "outputId": "d17bf872-8287-453b-cff0-3bda998bb602"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Recompute the linear filter using the FULL autocorrelation matrix (off-diagonals included)\n",
        "# This whitens the stimulus and yields a sharper, less biased filter estimate\n",
        "w_lin_ac = STA @ inv(stim_auto_corr)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Apply the corrected filter to the test set and clip negative rates with ReLU\n",
        "f_relu_ac = np.maximum(w_lin_ac @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b, 0)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pearson correlation on the test set\n",
        "perf_relu_ac = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_relu_ac / dt)[0, 1]\n",
