      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "72d3d392"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 11. LN Model — Exponential Nonlinearity (Gradient Descent)\n",
        "\n",
        "The **Poisson LN model** replaces the ReLU with a smooth exponential nonlinearity, guaranteeing strictly positive rates and enabling maximum-likelihood estimation:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$f(t) = \\exp\\!\\left(\\sum_\\tau w(\\tau)\\,\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau) + b\\right)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $f(t)$ is the predicted firing rate (spikes/bin) at time $t$ — always $> 0$\n",
        "- $w(\\tau)$ is the filter weight at lag $\\tau$; $\\mathbf{w}$ collects all weights into a vector\n",
        "- $\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$ is the z-scored stimulus $\\tau$ bins before $t$\n",
        "- $b$ is a scalar bias (interpretable as the log of the baseline firing rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "Under a Poisson spiking assumption, the log-likelihood of observing $r(t)$ spikes is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$L = \\frac{1}{T}\\sum_t \\Bigl[ r(t)\\ln f(t) - f(t) \\Bigr]$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $L$ is the mean Poisson log-likelihood over training time bins\n",
        "- $r(t)$ is the observed mean spike count at time $t$\n",
        "- $T$ is the number of training time bins\n",
        "\n",
        "We maximise $L$ by gradient ascent with the following gradients:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\nabla_w L = \\frac{1}{T}\\sum_t \\bigl(r(t) - f(t)\\bigr)\\,\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial b} = \\frac{1}{T}\\sum_t \\bigl(r(t) - f(t)\\bigr)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $\\nabla_w L$ is the gradient of $L$ with respect to each filter weight $w(\\tau)$\n",
        "- $r(t) - f(t)$ is the residual between observed and predicted spike counts\n",
        "- $\\eta$ is the learning rate (step size); weights are updated as $\\mathbf{w} \\leftarrow \\mathbf{w} + \\eta\\,\\nabla_wL$\n"
      ],
      "id": "72d3d392"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Compute"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sd0gwyXiVUPD"
      },
      "id": "sd0gwyXiVUPD"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "358371a2"
      },
      "source": [
        "N_iter = 500    # number of gradient-descent iterations\n",
        "eta    = 1e-1   # learning rate (step size)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialise weights near zero to break symmetry, bias at zero\n",
        "w_ln = 1e-9 * np.random.randn(integration_time)   # filter weights, shape (integration_time,)\n",
        "b_ln = 0.0                                          # bias scalar\n",
        "\n",
        "T_tr = len(time_tr)   # number of training bins (for gradient normalisation)\n",
        "T_te = len(time_te)   # number of testing  bins\n",
        "\n",
        "L_tr = np.zeros(N_iter)   # store training log-likelihood at each iteration\n",
        "L_te = np.zeros(N_iter)   # store testing  log-likelihood at each iteration\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(N_iter):\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Forward pass: predicted firing rate under the exponential nonlinearity\n",
        "    f_tr = np.exp(w_ln @ full_stim[time_tr, :].T + b_ln)   # shape (T_tr,)\n",
        "    f_te = np.exp(w_ln @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln)   # shape (T_te,)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Poisson log-likelihood: E[r*log(f) - f]  (up to a constant)\n",
        "    L_tr[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_tr) * r_tr - f_tr)   # scalar — training LL\n",
        "    L_te[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_te) * r_te - f_te)   # scalar — test LL (monitoring only)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Gradients of the log-likelihood w.r.t. weights and bias\n",
        "    dL_w = (r_tr - f_tr) @ full_stim[time_tr, :] / T_tr   # shape (integration_time,)\n",
        "    dL_b = np.sum(r_tr - f_tr) / T_tr                      # scalar\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Gradient ascent update (we maximise, not minimise)\n",
        "    w_ln += eta * dL_w\n",
        "    b_ln += eta * dL_b\n"
      ],
      "id": "358371a2",
      "outputs": [],
      "execution_count": null
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Plot"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "IUHJHcOAVTKo"
      },
      "id": "IUHJHcOAVTKo"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "# Figure 7 — training and test log-likelihood curves across iterations\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n",
        "fig.suptitle('Figure 7 — LN Model (exp): Training Curve', fontsize=15)\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.plot(L_tr, '--', linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[4], label='Log-L train')   # dashed = train\n",
        "ax.plot(L_te,       linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[4], label='Log-L test')    # solid  = test\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Log-Likelihood')\n",
        "ax.set_title('LN model (exp) — Training curve')\n",
        "ax.legend(loc='lower right')\n",
        "\n",
