    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6f47f85e"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 12. Smoothness Regularisation (Laplacian)\n",
        "\n",
        "Without regularisation the gradient-descent filter can be noisy. We add a **Laplacian** penalty that penalises large differences between adjacent filter weights, favouring smooth temporal profiles:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$L_{\\text{reg}} = L - \\frac{\\lambda}{2}\\,\\mathbf{w} L \\mathbf{w}^\\top$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $L_{\\text{reg}}$ is the regularised objective to be maximised\n",
        "- $L$ is the unregularised Poisson log-likelihood (Section 11)\n",
        "- $\\lambda$ is the regularisation strength — larger $\\lambda$ produces a smoother filter; it should be tuned on a held-out validation set\n",
        "- $\\mathbf{w}$ is the filter weight vector of length $T_{\\text{int}}$\n",
        "- $L$ is the Laplacian (second-difference) matrix of shape $(T_{\\text{int}} \\times T_{\\text{int}})$, with $L_{ii}=4$, $L_{i,i\\pm1}=-1$ (boundary entries $= 2$)\n",
        "- $\\mathbf{w} L \\mathbf{w}^\\top$ is a scalar penalty proportional to $\\sum_\\tau (w(\\tau)-w(\\tau+1))^2$, which is large when the filter oscillates rapidly\n",
        "\n",
        "The regularised gradient is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\nabla_w L_{\\text{reg}} = \\nabla_w L - \\lambda\\,\\mathbf{w} L$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $\\nabla_w L$ is the unregularised gradient (Section 11)\n",
        "- $\\lambda\\,\\mathbf{w} L$ is the gradient of the penalty term — it pulls adjacent weights closer together\n"
      ],
      "id": "6f47f85e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Compute"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9S0SjGuJVP2V"
      },
      "id": "9S0SjGuJVP2V"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "37df5c28",
        "outputId": "d1c54c19-a7f0-4d8b-f73c-ab8c11521a84"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Build the Laplacian (second-difference) matrix of size (integration_time x integration_time)\n",
        "# L[i,i] = 4, L[i,i±1] = -1  (interior); boundary entries are 2 instead of 4\n",
        "L_mat = 4 * np.eye(integration_time)                              # main diagonal\n",
        "L_mat -= np.diag(np.ones(integration_time - 1), 1)               # upper off-diagonal\n",
        "L_mat -= np.diag(np.ones(integration_time - 1), -1)              # lower off-diagonal\n",
        "L_mat[0, 0]   = 2   # boundary correction: first element\n",
        "L_mat[-1, -1] = 2   # boundary correction: last element\n",
        "\n",
        "lambda_reg = 0.15   # regularisation strength — controls smoothness vs data fit\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialise weights and bias for the regularised model\n",
        "w_ln_reg = 1e-9 * np.random.randn(integration_time)   # shape (integration_time,)\n",
        "b_ln_reg = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "L_tr_reg = np.zeros(N_iter)   # regularised training LL per iteration\n",
        "L_te_reg = np.zeros(N_iter)   # regularised test     LL per iteration\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(N_iter):\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Forward pass with current regularised filter\n",
        "    f_tr_reg = np.exp(w_ln_reg @ full_stim[time_tr, :].T + b_ln_reg)   # shape (T_tr,)\n",
        "    f_te_reg = np.exp(w_ln_reg @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln_reg)   # shape (T_te,)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Regularised log-likelihood: standard LL minus smoothness penalty\n",
        "    L_tr_reg[i] = (np.mean(np.log(f_tr_reg) * r_tr - f_tr_reg)\n",
        "                   - 0.5 * lambda_reg * w_ln_reg @ L_mat @ w_ln_reg)   # scalar\n",
        "    L_te_reg[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_te_reg) * r_te - f_te_reg)          # no penalty on test\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Gradient of regularised LL: standard gradient minus Laplacian penalty gradient\n",
        "    dL_w = ((r_tr - f_tr_reg) @ full_stim[time_tr, :] / T_tr\n",
        "            - lambda_reg * w_ln_reg @ L_mat)   # shape (integration_time,)\n",
        "    dL_b = np.sum(r_tr - f_tr_reg) / T_tr      # scalar\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Gradient ascent update\n",
        "    w_ln_reg += eta * dL_w\n",
        "    b_ln_reg += eta * dL_b\n",
        "\n",
        "# Evaluate regularised model on the test set\n",
        "f_ln_reg_te = np.exp(w_ln_reg @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln_reg)   # shape (T_te,)\n",
        "perf_ln_reg = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_ln_reg_te / dt)[0, 1]             # Pearson r\n",
        "print(f\"Performance — LN model + regularisation:  r = {perf_ln_reg:.3f}\")\n"
      ],
      "id": "37df5c28",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Performance — LN model + regularisation:  r = 0.716\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "execution_count": null
    },
