    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c069f289"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 13. LN Model — Softplus Nonlinearity\n",
        "\n",
        "**Softplus** is a smooth approximation of ReLU that is differentiable everywhere, making gradient-based optimisation more stable near zero:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{softplus}(x) = \\log(1 + e^x)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $x$ is the scalar pre-activation input to the nonlinearity\n",
        "\n",
        "Its derivative is the **sigmoid** function:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\frac{d}{dx}\\text{softplus}(x) = \\sigma(x) = \\frac{1}{1+e^{-x}}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $\\sigma(x)$ is the sigmoid (logistic) function, valued between 0 and 1\n",
        "\n",
        "The pre-nonlinearity input and predicted rate at each time step are:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$u(t) = \\mathbf{w} \\cdot \\tilde{X}(t) + b, \\qquad f(t) = \\text{softplus}\\bigl(u(t)\\bigr)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $u(t)$ is the linear pre-activation at time $t$ — the dot product of the filter with the stimulus history plus the bias\n",
        "- $f(t)$ is the predicted firing rate — always $> 0$ since $\\text{softplus}(x) > 0$ for all $x$\n",
        "- $\\mathbf{w}$ is the filter weight vector, $\\tilde{X}(t)$ is the stimulus history row, $b$ is the bias\n",
        "\n",
        "The gradient of the Poisson log-likelihood with respect to the filter weights is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\nabla_w L = \\frac{1}{T}\\sum_t \\left(\\frac{r(t)}{f(t)} - 1\\right) \\sigma(u(t))\\,\\tilde{x}(t-\\tau)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $r(t)$ is the observed mean spike count at time $t$\n",
        "- $\\frac{r(t)}{f(t)} - 1$ is the residual term — positive when the model under-predicts, negative when it over-predicts\n",
        "- $\\sigma(u(t))$ is the chain-rule factor from differentiating softplus with respect to $u(t)$\n",
        "- $T$ is the number of training time bins\n"
      ],
      "id": "c069f289"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 331
        },
        "id": "393fa14e",
        "outputId": "81da2165-a9c3-4328-fc1b-09788352bc0d"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Define softplus and its derivative (sigmoid) as lambda functions\n",
        "softplus  = lambda x: np.log1p(np.exp(x))          # log(1 + e^x)\n",
        "dsoftplus = lambda x: 1.0 / (1.0 + np.exp(-x))     # sigmoid: d/dx softplus = sigma(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialise softplus model weights and bias near zero\n",
        "w_ln_sp = 1e-9 * np.random.randn(integration_time)   # shape (integration_time,)\n",
        "b_ln_sp = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "L_tr_sp = np.zeros(N_iter)   # training LL per iteration\n",
        "L_te_sp = np.zeros(N_iter)   # test     LL per iteration\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(N_iter):\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Linear projection of stimulus history onto current filter (pre-nonlinearity)\n",
        "    u_tr = w_ln_sp @ full_stim[time_tr, :].T + b_ln_sp   # shape (T_tr,) — \"input\" to nonlinearity\n",
        "    u_te = w_ln_sp @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln_sp   # shape (T_te,)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Apply softplus nonlinearity to get predicted firing rates\n",
        "    f_tr_sp = softplus(u_tr)   # shape (T_tr,)\n",
        "    f_te_sp = softplus(u_te)   # shape (T_te,)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Poisson log-likelihood: E[r*log(f) - f]\n",
        "    L_tr_sp[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_tr_sp) * r_tr - f_tr_sp)   # training scalar\n",
        "    L_te_sp[i] = np.mean(np.log(f_te_sp) * r_te - f_te_sp)   # test scalar\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Gradient via chain rule: dLL/du * du/dw\n",
        "    # dLL/df = r/f - 1 ;  df/du = dsoftplus(u) = sigma(u)\n",
        "    dL_w = ((r_tr / f_tr_sp - 1) * dsoftplus(u_tr)) @ full_stim[time_tr, :] / T_tr\n",
        "    dL_b = np.sum((r_tr / f_tr_sp - 1) * dsoftplus(u_tr)) / T_tr   # scalar\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Gradient ascent update\n",
        "    w_ln_sp += eta * dL_w\n",
        "    b_ln_sp += eta * dL_b\n",
        "\n",
        "# Final test-set prediction with the softplus model\n",
        "f_ln_sp_te = softplus(w_ln_sp @ full_stim[time_te, :].T + b_ln_sp)   # shape (T_te,)\n",
        "perf_sp = np.corrcoef(psth_te, f_ln_sp_te / dt)[0, 1]                  # Pearson r\n",
        "print(f\"Performance — LN model (softplus):  r = {perf_sp:.3f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Figure 9 — left: exp vs softplus filters; right: predictions vs data\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 4))\n",
        "fig.suptitle('Figure 9 — Softplus Model: Filter and Prediction', fontsize=15)\n",
        "\n",
        "tau = np.arange(-integration_time + 1, 1) * dt   # lag axis in seconds\n",
        "\n",
        "# Left panel: overlay the exp-nonlinearity filter and the softplus filter\n",
        "axes[0].plot(tau, w_ln,    linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[4], label='w LN exp')       # exp model\n",
        "axes[0].plot(tau, w_ln_sp, linewidth=2, color=MAT_COL[5], label='w LN softplus')  # softplus model\n",
        "axes[0].axhline(0, color='k', linestyle='--')   # zero reference\n",
        "axes[0].set_xlabel('Past time (s)')\n",
        "axes[0].set_ylabel('Filter weight')\n",
        "axes[0].set_title('Filter: exp vs softplus')\n",
        "axes[0].legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Right panel: compare both model predictions to the measured PSTH\n",
        "axes[1].plot(time_te * dt, psth_te,          linewidth=2,   color=MAT_COL[1], label='Data')\n",
        "axes[1].plot(time_te * dt, f_ln_te   / dt,   linewidth=1.5, color=MAT_COL[4], label='LN exp')\n",
